verses.text: In the tenth year , in the tenth \add month\add*, in the twelfth \add day\add* of the month , the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came unto me, saying ,
Son of man , set thy face against Pharaoh king of Egypt , and prophesy against him, and against all Egypt :

Speak , and say , Thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; Behold, I \add am\add* against thee, Pharaoh king of Egypt , the great dragon that lieth in the midst of his rivers , which hath said , My river \add is\add* mine own, and I have made \add it\add* for myself.

But I will put hooks in thy jaws , and I will cause the fish of thy rivers to stick unto thy scales , and I will bring thee up out of the midst of thy rivers , and all the fish of thy rivers shall stick unto thy scales.

And I will leave thee \add thrown\add* into the wilderness , thee and all the fish of thy rivers : thou shalt fall upon the open fields ; thou shalt not be brought together , nor gathered : I have given thee for meat to the beasts of the field and to the fowls of the heaven.\f + \fr 29.5 \ft open…: Heb. face of the field\f*
And all the inhabitants of Egypt shall know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, because they have been a staff of reed to the house of Israel.
When they took hold of thee by thy hand , thou didst break , and rend all their shoulder : and when they leaned upon thee, thou brakest , and madest all their loins to be at a stand. \p
¶ Therefore thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; Behold, I will bring a sword upon thee, and cut off man and beast out of thee.

And the land of Egypt shall be desolate and waste ; and they shall know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: because he hath said , The river \add is\add* mine, and I have made \add it\add*.

Behold, therefore I \add am\add* against thee, and against thy rivers , and I will make the land of Egypt utterly waste \add and\add* desolate , from the tower of Syene even unto the border of Ethiopia.\f + \fr 29.10 \ft utterly…: Heb. wastes of waste\f*\f + \fr 29.10 \ft from…: or, from Migdol to Syene\f*\f + \fr 29.10 \ft Syene: Heb. Seveneh\f*
No foot of man shall pass through it, nor foot of beast shall pass through it, neither shall it be inhabited forty years.

And I will make the land of Egypt desolate in the midst of the countries \add that are\add* desolate , and her cities among the cities \add that are\add* laid waste shall be desolate forty years : and I will scatter the Egyptians among the nations , and will disperse them through the countries. \p
¶ Yet thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; At the end of forty years will I gather the Egyptians from the people whither they were scattered :

And I will bring again the captivity of Egypt , and will cause them to return \add into\add* the land of Pathros , into the land of their habitation ; and they shall be there a base kingdom.\f + \fr 29.14 \ft habitation: or, birth\f*\f + \fr 29.14 \ft base: Heb. low\f*
It shall be the basest of the kingdoms ; neither shall it exalt itself any more above the nations : for I will diminish them, that they shall no more rule over the nations.

And it shall be no more the confidence of the house of Israel , which bringeth \add their\add* iniquity to remembrance , when they shall look after them: but they shall know that I \add am\add* the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*. \p

¶ And it came to pass in the seven and twentieth year , in the first \add month\add*, in the first \add day\add* of the month , the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* came unto me, saying ,

Son of man , Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon caused his army to serve a great service against Tyrus : every head \add was\add* made bald , and every shoulder \add was\add* peeled : yet had he no wages , nor his army , for Tyrus , for the service that he had served against it:

Therefore thus saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*; Behold, I will give the land of Egypt unto Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon ; and he shall take her multitude , and take her spoil , and take her prey ; and it shall be the wages for his army.\f + \fr 29.19 \ft take her spoil…: Heb. spoil her spoil, and prey her prey\f*

I have given him the land of Egypt \add for\add* his labour wherewith he served against it, because they wrought for me, saith the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 29.20 \ft for his…: or, for his hire\f* \p

¶ In that day will I cause the horn of the house of Israel to bud forth , and I will give thee the opening of the mouth in the midst of them; and they shall know that I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
